sentences: María Victoria Ledesma Cuevas (born 30 May 1931), known by her stage name Rosa de Castilla (Spanish pronunciation: [ˈrosa ðe kasˈtiʎa]), is a Mexican singer and actress.
De Castilla made her film debut in Julián Soler's Los tres alegres compadres (1952), starring Jorge Negrete, Pedro Armendáriz, and Andrés Soler.
El lobo solitario, La justicia del lobo, and Vuelve el lobo (all in 1952).

Other notable films she appeared in during the late 1950s are the Mexiscope productions of Yo... el aventurero (1959) and Tan bueno el giro como el colorado (1959).
